# PromptWire (ProcessWire content)

This site uses **PromptWire** MCP (`pw_*` tools) to push and pull CMS content between local dev and remote. Docs: [PromptWire v1](https://www.peterknight.digital/docs/promptwire/v1/).

## Default assumption

When asked to change **page content** (copy, blog posts, field values, SEO meta, CMS-managed navigation), use PromptWire — not direct DB access, not guessing values from templates alone, and not hand-authoring `site/assets/pw-mcp/` without `pw_page_pull` or `pw_page_new`.

## Use PromptWire for

| Task | Tools |
|------|-------|
| Edit existing content | `pw_page_pull` → edit sync files → `pw_page_push` (dry-run first) |
| New page | `pw_page_new` → edit → `pw_page_publish` |
| Bulk section | `pw_pages_pull` / `pw_pages_push` |
| Inspect live content or schema | `pw_get_page`, `pw_query_pages`, `pw_search`, `pw_list_templates` |
| Schema changes | `pw_schema_pull`, `pw_schema_push`, `pw_schema_diff` |
| Images / file fields | `pw_file_sync`, `pw_page_assets` |

## Edit source files for

- PHP templates (`site/templates/`), modules, hooks, CSS/JS
- Rendering logic — not CMS field values stored in the database

## MCP servers

Use the PromptWire MCP entry that matches the target (local dev vs production). Names vary per project — check `.cursor/mcp.json`. Confirm before `targets: remote` or `both`.

## Sync files (`site/assets/pw-mcp/`)

- Never edit `page.meta.json` manually
- Rich text: `fields/*.html` and `matrix/` files referenced from `page.yaml`
- Page refs: only `id` in `_pageRef` blocks is editable; `_comment` is display-only

## Safety

- Push defaults to dry-run — preview before `dryRun: false`
- Default push target is local — confirm before production
